  "bib_entries": {
    "119340207": {
      "title": "Dilaton axion hair for slowly rotating Kerr black holes",
      "abstract": "Abstract Campbell et al. demonstrated the existence of axion \u201chair\u201d for Kerr black holes due to the non-trivial Lorentz Chern-Simons term and calculated it explicitly for the case of slow rotation. Here we consider the dilaton coupling to the axion field strength. consistent with low energy string theory and calculate the dilaton \u201chair\u201d arising from this specific axion source."
